<div id="review_204683112" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/204683112" />
    <a title="Diane" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3015634-diane"><img alt="Diane" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/204683112?book_show_action=true">Sep 02, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Diane" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Diane" href="/user/show/3015634-diane">Diane</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer204683112" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4050827759171338619">Either this is not one of Alice Hoffman&apos;s bests or I have just tired of Hoffman&apos;s flowery style and silly plots. The story of a woman who impulsively marries the wrong man, they have a child, she gets pregnant with another man, she dies, the husband has an affair with the neighbor while his wife is dying, needless to say, the two children are totally messed up. The problem is not only is the plot riduclous but I didn&apos;t like any of the characters, so their tragedies and tramas didn&apos;t evoke much s</span>
  <span id="freeText4050827759171338619" style="display:none">Either this is not one of Alice Hoffman's bests or I have just tired of Hoffman's flowery style and silly plots. The story of a woman who impulsively marries the wrong man, they have a child, she gets pregnant with another man, she dies, the husband has an affair with the neighbor while his wife is dying, needless to say, the two children are totally messed up. The problem is not only is the plot riduclous but I didn't like any of the characters, so their tragedies and tramas didn't evoke much sympathy. I only finished the book because I was desperate - away from home, visiting friends whose bookshelves were full of books I had read. This was the only one I could find that I hadn't read. I should have reread one of the others. Don't waste your time on this one.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4050827759171338619" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


