<div id="review_460824844" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/460824844" />
    <a title="Cheryl" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11255849-cheryl"><img alt="Cheryl" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1565547225p2/11255849.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/460824844?book_show_action=true">Nov 21, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cheryl" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cheryl" href="/user/show/11255849-cheryl">Cheryl</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780316017879" href="/book/show/1081181.Skylight_Confessions">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11255849-cheryl?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11255849-cheryl?shelf=fav-authors">fav-authors</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer460824844" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17958557844700299289">Whenever I need a moment to leave the real world and enter the magical, I go to authors like Alice Hoffman and Kate Morton. <br/><br/>Once again, Hoffman does not disappoint. <br/><br/>This is a book that is as real as it is magical. Starting with a young girl whose sick father has just died so she tells herself that the next man who walks down her street will become her husband, the book will have you bemused and electrified. It is an American fairy tale based on reality and set in Connecticut. <br/><br/>The fabulous house:</span>
  <span id="freeText17958557844700299289" style="display:none">Whenever I need a moment to leave the real world and enter the magical, I go to authors like Alice Hoffman and Kate Morton. <br /><br />Once again, Hoffman does not disappoint. <br /><br />This is a book that is as real as it is magical. Starting with a young girl whose sick father has just died so she tells herself that the next man who walks down her street will become her husband, the book will have you bemused and electrified. It is an American fairy tale based on reality and set in Connecticut. <br /><br />The fabulous house: the Glass Slipper. The rich suburban couple. The dysfuntional family. The mystery that stars with the red-haired mother, Arlyn (my favorite character). Her mysterious and melancholic son, Sam. Her daughter, Bee (or Blanca) my second favorite character. The father, John Moody--how appropriate of a name because John was indeed moody. <br /><br />What happens when your true love was right before your eyes and you never saw or appreciated her all along? <br /><br />Alice Hoffman said that she writes from "a subconscious place, it's almost like the elements of a dream." That's exactly how I feel when I read her books and though I didn't like this one as much as I did <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10950924.The_Dovekeepers" title="The Dovekeepers by Alice Hoffman" rel="nofollow noopener">The Dovekeepers</a>, I like how she never fails to take me away. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17958557844700299289" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


