        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3489530220" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2689638469308594935">I recall reading a collection of short stories by Alice Hoffman years ago, and they must have been good enough to prompt me to buy her books at library sales. Or perhaps my tastes have changed because I find everything I&apos;ve read by her since to be especially gloomy. Her writing is kind of like finding a bag of chips in the back of your cupboards. At first you&apos;re elated because who doesn&apos;t like an unexpected treat. But her writing, like chips, is junk food. Stale junk food at that. So if you find</span>
  <span id="freeText2689638469308594935" style="display:none">I recall reading a collection of short stories by Alice Hoffman years ago, and they must have been good enough to prompt me to buy her books at library sales. Or perhaps my tastes have changed because I find everything I've read by her since to be especially gloomy. Her writing is kind of like finding a bag of chips in the back of your cupboards. At first you're elated because who doesn't like an unexpected treat. But her writing, like chips, is junk food. Stale junk food at that. So if you find an occasional chip that doesn't taste stale, i.e. a paragraph or page-worth of writing that holds your interest, well, consider yourself lucky.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2689638469308594935" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
